\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory security controls for mobile devices and remote access technologies connecting to Elko County Information Systems.
 This policy ensures the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of County data,
 including Criminal Justice Information (CJI),
 by defining strict configuration,
 authorization,
 and usage requirements for wireless networking,
 remote connectivity,
 and mobile computing assets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations personnel,
 employees,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and agents who utilize mobile devices or remote access technologies to access County information assets.
 This scope includes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Agency-Controlled Devices
\series default
:
 Devices owned,
 leased,
 and managed by Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Remote Access Connections
\series default
:
 Any logical connection originating from outside the County's internal trusted network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Wireless Infrastructure
\series default
:
 All wireless access points (APs) and clients managed by the County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Personally Owned Devices
\series default
:
 Personally owned devices are strictly prohibited from accessing CJI or internal County network infrastructure.
 Limited access to non-CJI cloud services (e.g.,
 Office 365 web access) via personally owned devices is permitted only if it does not require full Mobile Device Management (MDM) enrollment,
 consistent with the Zero Support Model defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall authorize all remote access methods and mobile device platforms prior to deployment.
 Shall approve the selection of MDM solutions,
 designate compelling operational needs for privileged remote access,
 and approve all Risk Acceptance Memos for deviations.
 Serves as the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) for CJI exception processing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall ensure validation testing for rogue wireless access points is performed quarterly.
 Shall review wireless access point logs,
 VPN connection logs,
 and remote desktop session logs at least monthly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
System and Network Administrators
\series default
:
 Shall configure and maintain the MDM and VPN infrastructure,
 apply critical security patches,
 route all remote access traffic through managed gateways,
 and change administrative passwords on wireless access points in accordance with established baselines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Users
\series default
:
 Shall physically protect mobile devices,
 immediately report lost or stolen devices to the Assistant IT Director,
 and initiate session locks before leaving devices unattended.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory.
 Failure to comply shall result in the immediate revocation of remote access privileges,
 seizure of non-compliant County devices,
 and disciplinary action up to and including termination of employment or contract.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Exceptions to this policy must be documented using a formal Risk Acceptance Memo,
 including compensating controls,
 and approved in writing by the IT Director in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Exceptions involving CJI shall not be granted if they violate FBI CJIS Security Policy requirements without written concurrence from the CJIS Systems Officer (CSO).
\end_layout

